Mrs. D. Spare my blushes. I do declare—I—don’t ask me ;

but I don’t think they have anything on them; not a rag. The

nasty beasts!

Mrs. D. Time enough, you old fool, you? Let me get it once;

and I’ll make the body fact enough to you. That for your con-

genitals ! that for your pauperalities and fiscal agents ! [Exit.]

The Oracles of Shakspeare ; with a Selection of Aphorisms

from the Same Author. By Robert Hamilton. Boston :

